The paper proposes an automated pulmonary nodule detection algorithm using deep learning techniques. The algorithm involves the use of 3D convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and fully convolutional networks (FCNs) for nodule detection and identification. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of hierarchical saliency and progressive resolution techniques suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and medical imaging (cs.MS, cs.MM) sub-categories.
